               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1">ጻድቃን፡ ዘጰራቅሊጦስ፡</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Ṣādǝqān za-Ṗarāqliṭos</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="en" corresp="#n1">The Righteous Ones of Ṗarāqliṭos</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n2">ሰማዕታተ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos</t:persName>
               <t:persName xml:lang="en" corresp="#n2">Martyrs  of Ṗarāqliṭos</t:persName>
               <t:floruit><t:note>The number of martyrs is reported to have been 777 (<t:ref type="mss" target="ESap046#21r"/>).</t:note></t:floruit>
               <t:residence>The group arrived in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgray</t:placeName> (<t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0030AP">ʿĀddaqāḥarsi Ṗarāqliṭos</t:placeName>) from  <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5969Tiberi">Tiberias (Ṭǝbǝryādos)</t:placeName> (according to the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5878MiraclesParaqlitos">Miracles</t:ref>)</t:residence>

               
               <t:death>The <t:date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Sane4">4th of Sane</t:date> is mentioned in MSS as the day of the martyrdom (commemoration
                  date) of the martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos (cp. <t:ref type="mss" target="ESap046#21r"/>).</t:death>
               
            </t:personGrp>
            
         </t:listPerson>
